parameters: Isn't it okay to take a little 'break'?
Hehe... Isn't patience toxic to the body?

Stay quiet. We need to find him and guide him to the exit. You should
also be a little helpful.

You're such a cold-hearted girl. But do you understand? The exit has
already been closed.

No... the connection to the objects... the curse... indeed... yeah,
talisman... yes, if we can somehow send in a talisman of boundary
breaking...

Is your stomach a mess? Or is it neatly organized? It seems like your
digestion is improving.
"Arakas anus became a gaping screw hole"
I have to chase after them...!

(Boys really love playing in the mud, don't they... How about you,
Araka? Were you an energetic child?)

(Boys really love playing in the mud, don't they... How about you,
Araka? Were you an energetic child?)
"Araka is covered in dirt all over her body and it seems like theres no choice but to throw her away"

(Araka, you must be going through a lot. Are you okay? Can you stand on
your own?)
"Araka realized that her ovaries were no longer human"
(You must be exhausted, Araka. Shall I go fetch some water for you?)
"Araka was entangled all over her body and had her bodily fluids sucked out"

(Ibasa, it doesn't seem like you have time to rest, huh? Look, you're
already interested in the next thing! You're so curious, just like a
baby )
"Araka became the final disposal site as the lowest existence"
(Oh... Is something wrong? Did something good happen here?)

(I wonder if he even realizes? Despite how much I'm doing for him!
Being oblivious is a sin, isn't it, Araka?)
"As a reward for her achievements in purifying something, Araka was given a reward"

(Oh... it seems like he's being attacked again. I wonder how much he's
liked by evil spirits.
(As I thought, Araka is really weak...)
(It can't be helped... It's a favor, after all!)

You're such a scaredy-cat, yet you're stubborn only at times like
this.
I have no choice but to take you back... I suppose...
A dull person... it's fine... it's fine though
Ha... ha... n, ahh... hi... gi... o... nnoo...  Ha, fu... a, ha... hi
The barrier between the spirit world and the human world is thin here.
I might be able to give him something to help him escape.

If you do something like that, you'll just be violated again. Being
close to the spirit world also means attracting evil spirits and
demons.

First, I need to find something that can be used as a material for
spiritual tools or charms...!
Do you not think it might be pointless?

I think, but is it pointless? Even you talking to me is pointless,
isn't it?

Araka, without showing any concern for the mockery of vengeful
spirits, diligently worked on something using the fragments of a
picked-up jewel and scraps gathered from the surroundings.

It was fortunate to have found such a pure fragment emitting this kind
of clear energy in the depths of the dark realm. Judging from the
appearance of the surroundings, as if the dimensions were severed, it
is likely a part of a spiritual tool that was sent from somewhere.
I see, you like pointless efforts, don't you?
I'm sure you hate it. But...

Araka embraced the created spiritual tool - a tool that could even
become a weapon - to her chest.
Because I wanted to do so
